The following is a reformatted
version of the full text of the policy statement released today
by the  Bank of Japan  in Tokyo.  At the Monetary Policy Meeting held today, the Policy Board
of the Bank of  Japan  decided, by a unanimous vote, to set the
following guideline for money market operations for the
intermeeting period:  The Bank of Japan will conduct money market operations so
that the monetary base will increase at an annual pace of about
60-70 trillion yen.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
